<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Key G, 4/4. Hymn has three strophes + bridge. LH "33" triads dominant.
- Bridge (bars 9-12) uses Bm and Em7 for darker color; Am adds chromaticism.
- Final bars return to bright G with C and D7 cadence.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- LH consistently holds D3 as common tone between G and D chords.
- RH ascends to G5 at bridge climax (bar 9-10).

TEXTURE ARC:
- Light pickup; balanced verse; richer bridge; full final G cadence.
-->
